# Hooks & Automation (Cursor)

Use project automation sparingly and safely.

## Principles

- Prefer explicit, reviewable automation over “magic.”
- Avoid automations that bypass safety checks or approvals.
- Keep automations scoped to well-defined, repeatable workflows (formatting, validation, reminders).

## Task tracking

For multi-step work, keep a structured task list so progress and intent stay clear, and so review/verification is straightforward.

